text=(:if authgroup @tas:)%0a%0a(:toggle id=gi show="show grading interface" hide="hide grading interface":)%0a%0a>>id=gi%3c%3c%0a%0a[[GradebookArticles.{$Name}|See article in gradebook]] \\%0a[[{$FullName}?action=diff|See all changes to article]]%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradeitem:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#gradingcomment:)%0a%0a>>%3c%3c%0a%0a----%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a[[!TypologyOfPhoneticContrasts]]%0a%0a!Tone Systems: Comparing English and Cherokee%0a%0a:Author: khushiw%0a%0a'''Summary:''' \\%0a%0a[[#summary]]%0a%0aComparing English, which is not a tonal language, with Cherokee, which is a tonal language.%0a%0a[[#summaryends]]%0a%0a----%0a[[#content]]%0a%0aTone is often used to convey a variety of meanings. In some languages, tone creates an implicit meaning -- essentially hinting at a certain context. In other languages, tone can explicitly change the meaning of a word because it is a part of the language in the first place. A language that explicitly changes the meaning of a word based on tone has a tone system. In this case, tone is characterized as a change in pitch. This change in pitch is specific to a certain word or syllable when used in terms of tone systems. Intonation, on the other hand, is the change in pitch over the course of an entire phrase, or sentence. %0a%0aThe three types of tone systems are no tone, simple tone, and complex tone. English is a language with no tone. Although tone exists in the case of a sentence, paragraph, or context. Tone does not explicitly change the meaning of any word in English. Conversely, Cherokee is a language with a simple tone system. The Cherokee tone system consists of a suprasegmental system with low tones, high tones, lowfall tones, and superhigh accents.%0a%0aI find the difference between tonal languages and atonal languages very interesting. I wonder how tonal languages evolved and if languages trend toward becoming more atonal for the sake of simplicity.%0a%0a[[#contentends]]%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Expansions:%0a[[#expansions]]%0a%0a[[#expansionsend]]%0a%0a----%0a%25red%25 '''Add an expansion:'''%0a%0a(:if [ exists GradebookExpansions.{$Name}-{$Author} || equal {$Author} {$:Author} ] :)%0a%0a(:else:)%0a%0a(:foxform Site.FoxForms#newexpansion:)%0a%0a(:ifend:)%0a%0a----%0a----%0a%0a!!Comments%0a%0a%0a%0a(:section: :)%0a(:Category: TypologyOfPhoneticContrasts:)
